        "text": "Late to the discussion, but a concrete thing I’ve seen work to gently enforce shared values around language use is <https:\/\/github.com\/silasary\/iwazaru_bot|Iwazaru>. It’s a discord bot that reacts with :speak_no_evil: when certain words are used - especially casual sexist or ableist language (words like “crazy” or using “hey guys” to address the community). It works because it just reminds everyone that it’s not the language we want, but it’s not the end of the world. The bot will also be wrong sometimes because it doesn’t understand the context, which actually makes it feel less dramatic when you get a monkey.",
